<li id="lithub_daily_widget-9" class="widget widget_lithub_daily_widget"><div class="lithub-daily-header"><a href="/category/lit-hub-daily/"><b>Lithub</b> Daily</a></div><h2 class="widgettitle">August 12, 2024</h2>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-august-12-2024/"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-241466 size-thumbnail" src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/08/ghiblifood-150x150.jpg" alt="ghibli food" width="150" height="150" /></a>
<ul>
 	<li><a href="https://www.atlasobscura.com/articles/food-and-fanfiction" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The power of fictional food</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://daily.jstor.org/printing-anarchy/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The image of an anarchist should</span><span style="font-weight: 400"> be a printer</span></a></li>
 	<li><a href="https://jacobin.com/2024/08/donald-trump-nostalgia-80s-aesthetic/" class="external" target="_blank"><span style="font-weight: 400">The aesthetics (and politics) of nostalgia</span></a></li>
</ul>
<a href="https://lithub.com/lit-hub-daily-august-12-2024/"><button>More News</button></a></li>
